<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL BUS COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, An injured student is led away after a school bus carrying seven 
students with "special needs" collided Friday morning with a car at Overland 
and Garfield avenues in Culver City when the car made a sharp left turn in 
front of it, police said. Three students, ages 21, 11 and 12, suffered cuts and 
bruises and were taken to Brotman Medical Center in Culver City. The driver of 
the car, Albert Stoltey, 65, of Culver City was in serious condition in the 
intensive-care unit at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center. GEORGE R. FRY / Los Angeles 
Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
