<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXXON OIL SPILL AND HIGHER GAS PRICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Murkowski's column confirms the shameful fact that we are a nation of oil 
junkies. We are willing to spoil pristine wilderness, destroy innocent wildlife 
and befoul our atmosphere with lung-choking hydrocarbons to feed our habit. 
</P>
<P>
If we stop pulling oil from Alaska we do not have to get it from foreign oil 
pushers. What we do have to do is embark on a national program of increased 
energy efficiency and alternative energy sources. The possibilities are there, 
all we need is a little imaginative leadership. All we need to do is stare the 
oil conglomerates in the eye and "just say no." 
</P>
<P>
SCOTT HERBERTSON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angles 
</P>
</TEXT>
