<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARGERS TO OPEN ON ROAD, CLOSE AT HOME DEC. 24 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers will start the 1989 National Football League season on the road 
the Sunday after Labor Day and finish at home on Christmas Eve day. 
</P>
<P>
In between, they will play a stretch of four 1988 playoff teams in four weeks 
and appear on national television only once. 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers will open at the Raiders Sept. 10. It will be the 15th time in 17 
seasons that the Chargers have opened on the road. They are 8-6 in those games. 
The Chargers' home opener will be the next week against Houston. Kansas City 
visits the following Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers will play consecutive games against 1988 playoff teams in Weeks 6 
through 9, facing the Seattle Seahawks twice in three weeks, the New York 
Giants and Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers' only nationally televised game is at 5 p.m. Sunday, Nov. 12, at 
home against the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
They will be on the road four of the final six weeks and close at home against 
Denver on Dec. 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
