<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CSUN TO PLAY FOR VOLLEYBALL CHAMPIONSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Northridge advanced to the championship match of the Ball State men's 
volleyball tournament with a 15-12, 12-15, 15-9, 18-16 semifinal victory over 
ninth-ranked Ball State on Friday at Muncie, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Samuelson had 28 kills and Neil Coffman added 21 for CSUN (10-18). The 
Matadors face Indiana-Purdue-Ft. Wayne, a 15-6, 3-15, 3-15, 15-11, 15-9 winner 
over George Mason, in tonight's final. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Canyons 4, Bakersfield 0 -- Michelle Ruffner pitched a four-hitter, striking 
out three, to lead Canyons in a crucial Western State Conference game at home. 
The win moved Canyons (16-13 overall, 6-1 in conference play) into sole 
possession of second place and dropped Bakersfield (5-2 in the WSC) into third. 
</P>
<P>
Ruffner did not walk a batter and twice worked out of bases-loaded jams. 
</P>
<P>
Debbie Barnard supplied all the offense Ruffner needed, slamming a three-run 
homer in the third inning. Debbie Rendall doubled and singled for Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
WOMENS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
UC Davis 6, CS Northridge 3 -- Kaliko Yandall, Caren Hasselo and Heather Miller 
won singles matches for the Lady Matadors (6-12) in a losing effort in the 
Pomona tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Claremont-Mudd-Scripps 7, Occidental 2 -- Mari Uchida beat Occidental's Sue 
Hulse, 3-6, 6-4, 7-5, and teamed with Heather Holben to defeat Stacy Harris and 
Kellie Wiggin, 6-4, 6-4, in a Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic 
Conference match at Claremont. 
</P>
</TEXT>
