<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAFT'S THOMAS ACHIEVES PASSING SCORE ON SAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dedan Thomas, an All-City Section point guard at Taft High, learned Friday that 
he had scored more than 700 on his Scholastic Aptitude Test as mandated by NCAA 
freshman entrance requirements. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas, who before his senior season signed a letter of intent to attend Nevada 
Las Vegas, scored less than 700 on his first attempt. 
</P>
<P>
In order to be eligible next season under the NCAA's Prop. 48, Thomas also will 
have to post a 2.0 grade-point average and meet core curriculum requirements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
