<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHEMICAL WAREHOUSE FIRE FORCES EVACUATION OF 1,500 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATTLEBORO, Mass. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire early Friday roared through a chemical company warehouse where toxic 
substances were stored, forcing the evacuation of 1,500 residents for several 
hours, officials said. A hazardous waste cleanup crew was called in to remove 
the drums of acetone and cyanide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
