</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSUL, Iraq 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hailing its war victories against Iran, Iraq put domestically produced missiles 
on show Friday at a festival in this northern city. 
</P>
<P>
The ground-to-ground missiles, with a range of 400 miles to 530 miles, are 
similar to those used to bombard Tehran before a U.N.-brokered cease-fire last 
August ended eight years of fighting. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the missiles, named Al Hussein and Al Abbas after the grandsons 
of the Prophet Mohammed, the Military Industries Ministry also displayed a tank 
said to have been manufactured completely in Iraq. 
