<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Castle &amp; Cooke Inc.: The Los Angeles-based holding company for Dole Food 
Co. and Oceanic Properties Inc. reported first-quarter net income of $12.5 
million, down 49% from the same period a year ago. Revenue inched up 2% to $563 
million. The firm attributed the results to a pretax provision of $10 million 
for anticipated costs associated with the temporary ban on the sale of Chilean 
fruit by the Food and Drug Administration in mid-March, lower residential sales 
in Hawaii and higher interest expense due to a combination of higher interest 
rates and additional debt incurred to support the company's capital investment 
program. 
</P>
