<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY'S TOP TEAMS TO COMPETE IN TRACK CHAMPIONSHIPS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 1,000 athletes from 42 area high schools will compete today in the 
Orange County Boys' Track and Field Championships at Rancho Santiago College. 
</P>
<P>
The meet will feature most of the county's top teams, including defending 
champion Canyon, Capistrano Valley, Edison, Santa Ana Valley and Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
Although some of the teams will not be at full strength -- about 30 county 
athletes will be competing in the prestigious Arcadia Invitational tonight at 
Arcadia High School -- the meet should include a majority of the county's track 
and field talent. 
</P>
<P>
Top individuals expected to compete include Louie Muniz, a hurdler, long 
jumper, sprinter and relay runner from Woodbridge; Joe White, one of the 
county's best sprinters from Capistrano Valley, and Loara high jumper Greg 
Ramsey. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo will play host to the meet, which is scheduled to begin with the 
long jump at 9 a.m. and conclude with the mile relay at 5 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
