<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE CYPRESS PLAYERS DECIDE ON COLLEGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three members of the Cypress College baseball team have made verbal commitments 
to attend four-year colleges next fall, Cypress Coach Scott Pickler said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Pitcher Jeff Patterson has agreed to attend Arizona State, outfielder Steve 
Gill will attend the University of Arizona and pitcher Dennis Burbank will 
attend Oklahoma State. 
</P>
<P>
All three plan to sign letters of intent Wednesday, the first day of the spring 
signing period. 
</P>
<P>
Gill, from El Dorado High School, leads Cypress with nine home runs this 
season. Patterson, from Loara High School, is 6-1 with a 4.39 earned-run 
average. Burbank, who attended Valencia High School and transferred to Cypress 
from Pepperdine last fall, is 8-4 with a 3.06 earned-run average. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
