<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOOKENDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Author Talk: Ann and Evan Maxwell, the husband and wife team who write the 
Fiddler mystery series under the pen name A.E. Maxwell, will appear at the 
"Whodunit" night sponsored by the Friends of the Santa Ana Public Library at 7 
p.m. Monday. The event is being held to celebrate National Library Week. The 
Maxwells' most recent book, "Just Enough Light to Kill," is the fourth in their 
Orange County-based mystery-thriller series. 
</P>
<P>
Sci-Fi: Jefferson Peters of the University of Michigan will discuss "Persuasive 
Science Fictional Worlds and the Rhetorics of Art and Science" at noon Thursday 
in the Babb Writing Center, Humanities Office Building, Room 126, UC Irvine. 
Peters is in California to participate in a conference on fantasy and science 
fiction at UC Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
Children's Literature: Three children's authors -- Adrienne Jones, Valerie 
Keyworth and Alice Schertle -- will speak at noon Thursday at the Newport Beach 
Public Library, 856 San Clemente Drive. Children's illustrators Marjory Davis 
and Neill Ketchum also will present a display of their works. 
</P>
</TEXT>
